cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.AR, cs.SE

The paper deals with the detection of microarchitectural attacks using deep learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also uses advanced recurrent neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with hardware-level security, which could place it in cs.AR (Architecture) or cs.SE (Software Engineering).
